journal_entry: The wind Easterly Went to Hospital had finger done up very severe pain
Made an other visit to the Doctors for the cure of my finger Exceedingly painful
A visit to the Doctor
Went to the Hospital to to stay until the cure of my finger
The pain Exceedingly great
Had finger lanced to the bone from middle point to End after the Doctors had held long consultation
Finger so badly inflamed the doctor dare not take it of
Finger and hand very badly inflamed. cloths wet in ice water laid on back of my hand to stop the inflamation from going up any higher.
Was removed in an arm chair up several flights of stairs to the upper part of the building. A long consultation of Doctors as to whether it was best to take my finger off
No inflamation in hand but for some reason un noon to me, the doctors have decided not to trouble my hand to day
In Hospital at Leghorn so much run down by exceedingly great pain I am unable to get of my bed not having strength to stand alone
In Hospital at Leghorn
In Hospital at Leghorn Italy
Belong to the Bark Tukalet of New York but have been put ashore in the Hospital on account of a lame hand and expect to have it taken of

NA

NA

Still in the hospital waiting patiently to be able to get back on board the Bark

journal_entry: The wind North North East. moderate snow storm call day First Snow for the Season wrote letter home.
local_place: City Hotel, Hancock County Superior Court, City Hotel
noteworthy: First snow! It's almost two months earlier than these days

journal_entry: The wind northerly. ground covered with snow. Trial of Millard & Lowell in Case of Larceny. The good stolen from the schr. zicave Fiske & Curtis owners and plaintiffs. L.A. Emery for plaintiff Geo.Peters for defendent. Verdict Gully Sentance 18 month Prison
local_place: City Hotel, Hancock County Superior Court, City Hotel

journal_entry: The wind westerly and warm all the snow melted. Trial of Lilas M. Dorr. V.S. Frederic Phofford Mr Emery for plaintiff Mr Haddock for defendent verdict for plaintiff
local_place: City Hotel, Hancock County Superior Court, City Hotel

journal_entry: The wind Northerly & pleasant No Trial cam before the Jury
local_place: City Hotel, Hancock County Superior Court, City Hotel

journal_entry: The wind Westerly met at 9 AM at the Court house the jury discharged and the Cout adj ourned Came home in the afternoon with N.H. Heiggins Jr.
local_place: City Hotel, Hancock County Superior Court, City Hotel

journal_entry: The wind Southerly went gunning with N.H. Higgins got 1 bird.
The wind North East and foggy. Went gunning. with N.H. Higgins in forenoon got four birds.
The wind South East and foggy
The wind S.S.East. and rainy in the forenoon work in shop on boat.
The wind South East and heavy rain allday painted the boat and finished work onher all ready to launch
The wind South West. Launched the boat. Went to District Mting
The wind Northerly work in shop
The wind North West. Cut boat sail and work in shop
The wind North West work all day making boat sail
The wind North West
The wind North West raped boat sail
The wind Southerly went gunning in forenoon
Moderate Southerly work all day around the School house.
The wind Easterly and foggy made spars for the boat and bent the boat sail
The wind Southerly work in shop
Very heavy Northerly winds went Gunning
The wind Northerly.
The wind North Easterly and moderate went gunning
The wind E.S.E heavy blow and big rain storm Went to Presidential election
The wind South South East. Fresh breeze and heavy rain work about home
The wind very moderate and overcast all day vary light air Northerly work about home
The wind North north. East. over cast and drizzling rain went gunning in forenoon work about home in the afternoon
The wind Easterly. foggy and drizzling rain. wrote Mortgage deed from Amaziah to Stephen Southard. In the afternoon Went to Bar Harbor in a boat to carry Elbridge Lyman over. came back at night.
location: Winter Harbor, Bar Harbor, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind Northerly, heavy rain all the forenoon in afternoon showery
The wind North work about home
The wind Northerly wrote letter to E.V. Lynam worked apart of the forenoon for C. J.Guflill
The wind North went gunning in forenoon. In the afternoon worked for G.W.Tracy on out buildings
The wind North North East. cold in morning Worked all day making flying jibboom for Schr. Black Warrior Reed letter from Wiswell & Wiswell
The wind moderate N.E. in forenoon Calm in afternoon Worked one half day on G.W. Tracy's out buildings wrote letter to Wiswell & Wiswell
The wind North East worked 1/2 day on out buildings for G.W. Tracy
The wind Easterly went on board the Schr Henrietta and went to Rockland to buy coal and provisions for winter. arrived at five oclock P.M. and went into Atlantic wharf.
The wind Easterly heavy blow laid at Atlantic wharf waiting for a channel to get into a berth to discharge wood.
The wind East North East over cast fresh breeze rainy by spells. To much wind to get into buth to discharge attended the Auction sale od Islands belonging to the State. Purchased Crow Island
The wind North East and moderate. Got into the berth to discharge at high water in the afternoon and took off deckhand.
Calm and misty all day finished onloading vessel in the forenoon. And in the afternoon took in Coal provisions for winters use. and got ready for home
The wind North East Started from the wharf at day light for home got heavy winds and went back. At 2 oclock in the afternoon got underway and went to Fox Island. under reefs wind North
The wind North fresh breeze got underway at sunrise under reefs and got home at 2 oclock P.M.
The wind North fresh breeze
The wind North West hauled the Schr Henrietta into the wharf and took out coal and hauled it home.
Heavy breeze to the Westward work in the shop
The wind WNWest took Steamer Chas Hougton and went to S.W. Harbor with my wife. took a boat and went to North East Harbor.
location: Winter Harbor, Southwest Harbor, Northeast Harbor

journal_entry: The wind W North West took small boat and went to Cranberry Isles to see Capt Thomas Bunker Came back in the Evening.
The wind North West. moderate winds and cold
The wind Northerly moderate and snowy in forenoon
The wind North West and cold.
The wind Northerly and Moderate
The wind Westerly and moderate
The wind South. West. Took Steamer Uelyses at South West Harbor and went to Sullivan and went home with my wife
The wind Westerly work in the afternoon for G.W. Tracy. wrote letter to Josiah Smallidge. and Hancock Citizen
The wind moderate westerly work at home in shop
The wind North East, and overcast in the afternoon snow storm. Reed deed of Crow Island. from state land agent. work at home in shop and putting besh around the house
The wind North West vary cold and blustering
The wind moderate Northerly and cold
The wind E.N. East. Snow storm all day work in shop.
Calm warm and pleasant in forenoon Fresh Southerly in afternoon. Went Clamming
Nearly Calm all day very moderate Southerly in afternoon
The wind Westerly fresh breeze. work in shop.
The wind blew South West. in forenoon and W.N.W. in afternoon very heavy blow
The wind West. North. West. heavy breeze and very cold
The wind Easterly sow storm in forenoon. rain in afternoon. work in shop making chair.
The wind Westerly and cold work about home
The wind West S. West Finished making chair
The wind Northerly Snowing in afternoon
The wind North North East went gunning on Turtle Island. snowing in forenoon
location: Winter Harbor, Turtle Island, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind North North. E Snowy all day.
The wind North West
The wind North West. Helped J F Kingsley in forenoon fixry born. went to Christmas three in the Evening.
Moderate. and calm all day warm. Had wooden wedding in the evening owing to the snow storm saturday it was put off.
The wind North West moderate all day. put row locks on G.W. Tracy's dora
The wind Westerly work in shop turning wood the wind mill
Calm in the morning then the wind breezed up to the Eastward work at the door cutting fire wood. In the evening heavy snow and rain storm with high winds
The wind Southerly. with snow squalls. Westerly in afternoon. Work at home cutting wood. and turning Lounge legs in shop
The wind Westerly and pleasant.
